A N A C T
RELATING TO TOWNS AND CITIES -- ACTIONS BY AND AGAINST TOWNS
Introduced By: Representatives Stewart, Morales, J. Lombardi, Cruz, Felix, Potter, and
Batista
Date Introduced: February 13, 2025
Referred To: House Municipal Government & Housing
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 45-15-5 of the General Laws in Chapter 45-15 entitled "Actions by
2 and Against Towns" is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 45-15-5. Presentment to council of claim or demand against town.
4 (a) Every person who has any money due him or her from any town or city, or any claim
5 or demand against any town or city, for any matter, cause, or thing whatsoever, shall take the
6 following method to obtain what is due: The person shall present to the town council of the town,
7 or to the city council of the city, a particular account of that personâ€™s claim, debt, damages, or
8 demand, and how incurred or contracted; which being done, in case just and due satisfaction is not
9 made to him or her by the town or city treasurer of the town or city within forty (40) days after the
10 presentment of the claim, debt, damages, or demand, the person may commence his or her action
11 against the treasurer for the recovery of the complaint.
12 (b) Within sixty (60) days of the close of their fiscal year, every municipality shall be
13 required to disclose on their official website the following information:
14 (1) The number of legal actions in which the municipality, or any official or employee of
15 the municipality sued or was sued in their official capacity, during the year;
16 (2) The case number for each legal action and the court in which it was filed;
17 (3) A short description of the legal claims asserted in the case;
18 (4) The current status of the case; and
19 (5) All costs and expenses related to the legal action in the following categories:

1 (i) Courts costs;
2 (ii) Legal fees;
3 (iii) Expert witness fees;
4 (iv) Compensatory and punitive damages; and
5 (v) Any other costs, fees or expenses incurred.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
